          "faqs": [
            {
              "question": "How much does a website cost?",
              "answer": "Starter sites begin at £2,500 (4–6 pages), growing business sites at £5,000 (8–12 pages with more features), and complex builds or integrations at £8,500+. You'll get a fixed-price quote tailored to your exact needs after a quick call — no hidden extras or surprises. Full details are in the Pricing section above.",
              "category": "Pricing"
            },
            {
              "question": "What platform or CMS do you use?",
              "answer": "I build with a modern, bespoke stack (Next.js/React with a structured content system) — no off-the-shelf templates or heavy platforms like WordPress. This keeps things fast and secure while giving you a simple, safe interface to edit text, images, pricing, and repeatable sections yourself.",
              "category": "Tech"
            },
            {
              "question": "How long does a typical project take?",
              "answer": "Most websites are ready to launch in 4–8 weeks from kickoff. More complex apps can take longer, but you'll get an exact timeline upfront before anything starts.",
              "category": "Process"
            },
            {
              "question": "What are the payment terms?",
              "answer": "Projects are fixed-price with a clear schedule agreed in your proposal. By default this is a 50% deposit to secure your start date, with the remaining 50% due when the site's ready for launch. Invoices are payable within 7 days. Full details are in the Terms of Service.",
              "category": "Pricing"
            },
            {
              "question": "What is your refund/cancellation policy?",
              "answer": "The deposit secures your slot and is non-refundable once work starts. If you cancel early, you'll only pay for work completed. Full details are in the proposal and Terms.",
              "category": "Pricing"
            },
            {
              "question": "What are the ongoing costs after launch?",
              "answer": "Nothing mandatory. Your first 12 months of hosting are included in the build price. After that, hosting is optional at £120/year if you want me to keep managing it (fast, secure servers with daily backups and monitoring). Support, updates, or new features are quoted separately as you need them — no hidden retainers or subscriptions.",
              "category": "Pricing"
            },
            {
              "question": "What's included in support — and what isn't?",
              "answer": "Support covers help with any issues from the original build (e.g., bugs or technical glitches) and general questions about using your site. It doesn't include new features, content updates, or major redesigns — those are quoted separately. Most clients handle day-to-day edits themselves, and only reach out occasionally for bigger changes.",
              "category": "Support"
            },
            {
              "question": "How many revisions are included?",
              "answer": "Enough to get it right. Typically one full review round on key pages plus reasonable tweaks during the build (layout, copy adjustments, etc.). The goal is a site you're happy with — we'll keep refining until it feels spot-on within the agreed scope.",
              "category": "Process"
            },
            {
              "question": "What if I need changes after launch?",
              "answer": "You can update text, images, and pricing yourself anytime using the straightforward admin area. For bigger structural changes, I'm happy to help with either ongoing support or one-off fixes.",
              "category": "Support"
            },
            {
              "question": "Will my site be accessible and mobile-friendly?",
              "answer": "Yes to both. Every site is built mobile-first (fully responsive across phones, tablets, and desktops) and meets WCAG 2.1 AA standards where practical. It's part of the \"NHS-grade rigour\" approach — things work properly for all visitors.",
              "category": "Tech"
            },
            {
              "question": "Can you migrate my existing site/content?",
              "answer": "Yes, happy to. For most projects I can bring over existing pages, images, blog posts, or products. We'll discuss what's needed during the discovery call and include it in the quote if required.",
              "category": "Logistics"
            },
            {
              "question": "Do you do ecommerce, bookings, or other integrations?",
              "answer": "Yes — depending on the complexity. I've built booking systems, member areas, payment integrations, and simple shops. If it fits your needs and budget, we can include it in the scope. More advanced ecommerce platforms (like full Shopify stores) I'd usually recommend a specialist, but straightforward solutions are no problem.",
              "category": "Tech"
            },
            {
              "question": "What do you need from me, and when?",
              "answer": "Mainly content (text, images, branding) and access (domain login if needed). I'll give you a clear checklist early on with suggested deadlines. The sooner you can supply things, the smoother and faster the project goes — but we can work around your schedule.",
              "category": "Process"
            },
            {
              "question": "Do you provide training or handover for editing the site?",
              "answer": "Yes — on completion you'll get admin access, a quick walkthrough (video call or written guide), and clear instructions tailored to your site. Most clients feel confident updating things themselves straight away.",
              "category": "Support"
            },
            {
              "question": "Can I see how editing works?",
              "answer": "Yes — I can share a short walkthrough showing how text, images, and sections are updated.",
              "category": "Support"
            },
            {
              "question": "Do you work with clients outside Oxford?",
              "answer": "Absolutely. Most clients are across the UK or international — everything works smoothly via video calls.",
              "category": "Logistics"
            },
            {
              "question": "Can you work with my existing hosting?",
              "answer": "Yes, no problem. Most prefer my managed setup, but I can deploy to yours.",
              "category": "Logistics"
            },
